data.enText: a line or small fold in your skin, especially on your face, that forms as you get older

data.chText: 她眼角上出现了鱼尾纹。
data.enText: There were fine wrinkles around her eyes.
a small fold that you do not want in a piece of cloth or paper
to make the skin on your face form into lines or folds; to form lines or folds in this way
She wrinkled up her nose in distaste.

data.chText: 他全神贯注地锁紧眉头。
data.enText: He wrinkled his brow in concentration.

data.chText: 他咧嘴一笑满脸都是皱纹。
data.enText: His face wrinkled in a grin.
to form raised folds or lines in an untidy way; to make sth do this

data.chText: 她长袜的膝盖处起了皱褶。
data.enText: Her stockings were wrinkling at the knees.

tr: a clever method of doing something (especially something new and different)

example: they finally have the wrinkles pretty well ironed out

tr: a slight depression in the smoothness of a surface
example: ironing gets rid of most wrinkles

tr: become wrinkled or crumpled or creased
make wrinkles or creases on a smooth surface
make a pressed, folded or wrinkled line in
example: crease the paper like this to make a crane

tr: gather or contract into wrinkles or folds

value.def: Wrinkles are lines which form on someone's face as they grow old.

example.ex: His face was covered with wrinkles...
Some deep wrinkles furrow his lower forehead.
example.tran: 他额头下方出现了几道深深的皱纹。

value.def: When someone's skin wrinkles or when something wrinkles it, lines start to form in it because the skin is getting old or damaged.

example.ex: The skin on her cheeks and around her eyes was beginning to wrinkle.
example.tran: 她两颊和双眼周围开始起了皱纹。

example.ex: ...protection against the sun's rays that age and wrinkle the skin.
example.tran: 防晒以免皮肤老化起皱

example.ex: I did indeed look older and more wrinkled than ever.
example.tran: 我的确比从前显老, 皱纹也多了。

value.def: A wrinkle is a raised fold in a piece of cloth or paper that spoils its appearance.

example.ex: He noticed a wrinkle in her stocking.
example.tran: 他注意到她长筒袜上有一道褶儿。

value.def: If cloth wrinkles, or if someone or something wrinkles it, it gets folds or lines in it.

example.ex: Her stockings wrinkled at the ankles...
example.tran: 她的长筒袜在脚踝处起了褶儿。

example.ex: His suit was wrinkled and he looked very tired.
example.tran: 他的西服皱巴巴的，整个人显得非常疲惫。

value.def: When you wrinkle your nose or forehead, or when it wrinkles, you tighten the muscles in your face so that the skin folds.

example.ex: Frannie wrinkled her nose at her daughter...
example.tran: 弗兰妮朝她女儿皱了皱鼻子。

example.ex: Ellen's face wrinkles as if she is about to sneeze.
example.tran: 艾伦的脸皱了起来，好像要打喷嚏。
